comments.body:
Good investigation!
Then, should we add a caution like below in release notes?

```
Before this release, staging path and publish path for CSI block volume were as follows:
- Staging path: plugins/kubernetes.io/csi/volumeDevices/staging/{pvname}
- Publish path: plugins/kubernetes.io/csi/volumeDevices/publish/{pvname}
In this release these are changed as follows:
- Staging path: plugins/kubernetes.io/csi/volumeDevices/staging/{volumeID}
- Publish path: plugins/kubernetes.io/csi/volumeDevices/publish/{volumeID}/{podUID}

As a result, upgrading Kubernetes cluster while any pods with CSI block volumes running on a node will cause these path inconsistent, which will lead failure in unstaging/unpublishing volume. 
Therefore, all nodes need to be drained before upgrading Kubernetes cluster.
```

Any improvements in wording are welcome.

